  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And when these beasts give glory,.... When they give God the glory of all his perfections, covenant, and promises, and of all the gifts and grace bestowed on them, and of the success of their ministry; and in it glorify Father, Son, and Spirit, who bear their respective parts in the business of salvation; and ascribe to each their due glory in election, redemption, and sanctification: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and honour; in the several parts of religious worship performed by them; and not with their lips only, but with their hearts also: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and thanks; for all blessings, temporal and spiritual, bestowed on them, and on the saints: even ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to him that sat on the throne; God the Father, Revelation 4:3; ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "to him that sat on the throne; God the Father, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Revelation 4:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "who liveth for ever and ever; he who is the living God, and will always continue so. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "who liveth for ever and ever; he who is the living God, and will always continue so. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "And when those beasts {c} give glory and honour and thanks to him that sat on the throne, who liveth for ever and ever,",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "And when those beasts ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{c}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " give glory and honour and thanks to him that sat on the throne, who liveth for ever and ever,",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(c) God is said to have glory, honour, kingdom, and such like given to him, when we godly and reverently set forth that which is properly and only his.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Meyer's NT Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 4:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὅταν δώσουσι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The fut., instead of the regular sub.,[1825] does not present a conception that is strictly future,[1826] but has, like the Heb. imperfect, the force of a frequentative: “when, as often as.”[1827]",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ΔΌΞΑΝ ΚΑῚ ΤΙΜῊΝ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "ΔΌΞΑΝ ΚΑῚ ΤΙΜῊΝ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Viz., the worshipful acknowledgment of the glory and honor[1828] belonging to the Lord;[1829] while by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ΚΑῚ ΕὐΧΑΡΙΣΤΊΑΝ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "ΚΑῚ ΕὐΧΑΡΙΣΤΊΑΝ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is designated immediately, and without metonymy, the thanksgiving[1830] rendered by the creature.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Τῶ ΚΑΘΗΜΈΝῼΑἸΏΝΩΝ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Τῶ ΚΑΘΗΜΈΝῼΑἸΏΝΩΝ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". So God calls the enthroned God very similarly as the four beasts praise him, and in the same respect. Hence, also on cemore in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 4:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the same designation of God, comprising the reason for the praise, and the ground of all hope and prophecy.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "On ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 4:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 5:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 19:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The casting-down of the crowns is, together with the falling down and worshipping, the sign of humiliation before the King and Lord, in whose presence no creature whatever has any glory or honor of its own.[1831]",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[1825] Winer, p. 289 sq.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[1826] From now, and to all the future. Cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 7:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " sq. It is not so earlier, because only since the work of redemption is in progress, and the victory of Christ in development, are the twenty-four elders in this position and occupation. De Wette; cf. Stern.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
